  "text": "Then at present it would seem that our life span is much too short for those who are new to third-density lessons. Is this correct? I am Ra. This is correct. Those entities which have, in some way, learned/taught themselves the appropriate distortions for rapid growth can now work within the confines of the shorter life span. However, the greater preponderance of your entities find themselves in what may be considered a perpetual childhood.",
